@NODE "New" "New in Adagis v4.1"
@TOC "MAIN"

@{b}New in v4.1@{ub}

-A couple of bugs killed.

-New 'Copy to clipboard' menu.

-The adage listview is automatically set to be the 'current' object, so you can scroll it using the keyboard.

-The 'Out of range' error in the Adagis AddOn should not appear anymore (I hope).

-Random number generation improved.

-New Adagis logo :-)

@ENDNODE


@NODE "What is Adagis" "What is Adagis"
@TOC "MAIN"

@{b}What is Adagis ?@{ub}

Well, Adagis can be described as a Fortune-Cookie program.
Its main purpose is to display a cookie (an adage) in a window of your workbench.

The cookies are stored in a data file. Adagis chooses one randomly (or not) and displays it.

This is a simple description. Just go on reading...
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Install" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"

@{b}Installation@{ub}

Very simple:

Just run the script English.install to install the program, the icon and the data file that you want where you want :-p.

You can choose which AddOn will you use and where should it be installed.
AmigaTechnologies recommends having all the files related to a program into a single dir. In Adagis 4 I've tried to follow this rule, so a drawer 'Adagis4' will be created.
This drawer contains the AddOns, the prefs program...

Probably in the future more Adagis features will me moved to AddOns, so having its' own dir will be more important.

Note: (for those who never look what they're installing)
I've changed the Adagis distribution. From now on Adagis will come in two files:
'Adagisv40_bin.lha' contains the prog, installation, icons and so.
'Adagisv10_dat.lha' contains the cookie-files.
This way, you'll not have to download the cookies you already have when downloading a new version of Adagis.

The version numbers are different because a new release of Adagis will not imply a new release of the data-files.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "How it works" "How it works"
@TOC "MAIN"

@{b}Using Adagis@{ub}

To use Adagis you need:

     -AmigaDOS v2.0+     (2.1+ -v37- required to use locale.library)
     -MUI v3.2+

